

	 
      the moon  like a widowed lady she shines her remorseful light upon the earth  when whole, she is round and proud, but often she is incomplete, she hides herself from the world  why does she do this?  what terrible event happened in her past to cause her such woe  and what are those marks upon her white face  are they memories, dark upon the light, bad against the good  are they terrible events she wants hidden in the sands of time  i'm afraid we shall never know  for in her fear she does not speak  so learn from the lady, do not cower and be silent, be strong and be heard  do not let the bad fade into the past for, like the lady, you will never be whole
    
